  "texts": [
    "I. INTRODUCTIONInformation and Communication Technologies (ICT) have gained unprecedented relevance in today's society, playing a crucial role in the creation and development of countless digital tools that have transformed various aspects of daily life, including education [1].",
    "This rapid technological evolution has created an urgent need for teachers to develop and possess appropriate digital competencies.",
    "These competencies are essential for teachers not only to effectively integrate into the digital environment but also to teach their students in a way that meets the demands and challenges of the 21st century.",
    "The ability to use these tools effectively allows educators to offer a more dynamic, interactive education that aligns with the emerging needs of contemporary society, thus preparing students to successfully navigate an increasingly digitalized world [2].The insufficient development of investigative competencies in regular basic education students is due to several factors, such as traditional teaching methods that prioritize memorization over inquiry [3], lack of resources and teacher training [4], rigid curricula that do not allow for creative activities [5], and low motivation and support in both school and family environments [6].",
    "The use of ChatGPT can mitigate these issues by providing instant access to a wide range of information and academic sources, facilitating autonomous exploration [7]."
  ],
